nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.eventscheduling

Interface SimEventInterface<T extends SimTime<?,?,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of simulation time, e.g. SimTimeCalendarLong or SimTimeDouble or SimTimeDoubleUnit.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSimEvent, LambdaSimEvent, SimEvent, SimEvent.CalendarDouble, SimEvent.CalendarFloat, SimEvent.CalendarLong, SimEvent.TimeDouble, SimEvent.TimeDoubleUnit, SimEvent.TimeFloat, SimEvent.TimeFloatUnit, SimEvent.TimeLong

    public interface SimEventInterface<T extends SimTime<?,?,T>>
extends java.io.Serializable
    A SimEventInterface embodies the envelope in which the scheduled method invocation information is stored.

      • getPriority

        short getPriority()
        Returns:
        The priority of a simulation event. The priorities are programmed according to the Java thread priority. Use 10 (MAX_PRIORITY), 9, .. , 5 (NORMAL_PRIORITY), 1(MIN_PRIORITY)
